"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-12-paris-2024-dtigress-kalu-named-to-olympics-basketball-second-team\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Ezinne Kalu has been selected for the 2024 Olympic Games women's basketball event second team.  Kalu was D'Tigress' top performer at the Paris Olympic Games.  The 32-year-old averaged 18.5 points, 3.0 rebounds, 4.0 assists, and 2.5 steals per game at the games.  Kalu is the first African to make the selection.  D'Tigress made a remarkable impact in Paris 2024, becoming the first African country to make it to the quarterfinals.  The African champions defeated Australia and Canada in the group stage.  D'Tigress head coach Rena Wakama was also named Best Coach in the women's basketball event.  Transfer: Samu Omorodion's move to Chelsea 'at risk'  Transfer: Chelsea confirm deal for Wiley  D'Tigress maintain 8th position in latest FIBA women's rankings  FIBA WWCQ: D'Tigress star Macaulay named in All-Star team  D'Tigress captain Ogoke retires from national team  FG fulfils pledge to D'Tigress for winning 2025 FIBA Women's Afrobasket  Kalu: Group demands thorough probe after LPDC dismissal of NYSC controversy  2026 FIBA World Cup Qualifiers: D'Tigress rally to 101-84 victory over Philippines  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"